Program: Last Word
Title: Cyril Stein, Alberto Granado, Rachel Cameron and Anthony Brooke
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00z6f34
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 Mar 2011
Matthew Bannister remembers: Cyril Stein, who built up Ladbrokes from one betting shop to a multi-billion pound business. Alberto Granado who travelled with Che Guevara on his famous motorcycle journey across South America. Rachel Cameron - doyen of ballet teachers - who passed on the ideas of Diaghilev. Necmettin Erbakan, Turkey's first Islamist prime minister. And the last white Rajah of Sarawak - Anthony Brooke. Show less